By
Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Vice
President Yemi Osinbajo on Monday presided over the Federal Executive Council
(FEC) meeting at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The FEC which until today
holds on Wednesday is to give way for the valedictory session of the current
cabinet slated for that day (Wednesday). It started around 10.02am
with the rendition of the National anthem. Minister of Water
Resource, Suleiman Adamu said the Muslim opening prayer while the Christian
opening prayer was offered by the Minister of State for Niger Delta Affairs. Recall that the current
cabinet is expected to hold its valedictory session on Wednesday. Inauguration of the
second term tenure of President Muhammadu Buhari’s government is slated for
29th of May 2019. Sundiata Post recalls
that Vice President Yemi Osinbajo presided over the meeting due to the absence
of President Muhammadu Buhari who went to Makkah, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia
last week to observe Umrah.